Date: 7/8/1999
Source: Listener (New Zealand Listener)
Author:
Vol / Page: 34
Edition:
Quote: Among the fearsome creatures that stalked New Zealand in days gone by was the pouakai - an eagle with a three-metre wing-span and the impact of a Mack truck. It preyed on the moa - and on humans - and is estimated to have been among the largest of all feathered predators.
